## ğŸ“– 1. Introduction

<div align="center">

### ğŸ§  From Thinking to Acting: The Rise of Agentic Reasoning

*Bridging thoughts and actions through autonomous agents that plan, act, and learn*

---

</div>

**Reasoning** is the cornerstone of intelligenceâ€”enabling inference, problem-solving, and decision-making. While large language models (LLMs) excel at reasoning in closed-world settings (mathematics, coding, benchmarks), they face fundamental challenges in **open-ended, dynamic real-world environments**.

### ğŸŒŸ The Paradigm Shift

The emergence of **agentic reasoning** represents a transformative leap: reframing LLMs as **autonomous agents** that don't just thinkâ€”they **plan, act, and learn** through continual interaction with their environment.

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Traditional LLM Reasoning] -->|Paradigm Shift| B[Agentic Reasoning]
    B --> C[Plan]
    B --> D[Act]
    B --> E[Learn]
    C --> F[Adaptive Intelligence]
    D --> F
    E --> F
```

### ğŸ¯ Survey Framework

This survey provides a **systematic roadmap** by organizing agentic reasoning along **three complementary dimensions**:

<table>
<tr>
<td width="33%" align="center">
<h4>ğŸ—ï¸ Environmental Dynamics</h4>
<b>3 Layers of Capability</b>
</td>
<td width="33%" align="center">
<h4>âš™ï¸ System Constraints</h4>
<b>2 Optimization Settings</b>
</td>
<td width="33%" align="center">
<h4>ğŸ¨ Real-World Impact</h4>
<b>Applications & Benchmarks</b>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top">

ğŸ”¹ **Foundational** - Core single-agent abilities (planning, tool-use, search) in stable environments

ğŸ”¹ **Self-Evolving** - Adaptation through feedback, memory, and learning in dynamic settings  

ğŸ”¹ **Collective** - Multi-agent coordination, role specialization, and collaborative intelligence

</td>
<td valign="top">

ğŸ”¸ **In-Context Reasoning** - Test-time scaling through structured orchestration and adaptive workflows

ğŸ”¸ **Post-Training Reasoning** - Behavior optimization via RL and supervised fine-tuning

</td>
<td valign="top">

ğŸ”¬ Scientific Discovery

ğŸ¤– Robotics & Embodied AI

âš•ï¸ Healthcare & Medicine

ğŸ” Autonomous Research

ğŸ’» Mathematical Reasoning

</td>
</tr>
</table>

### ğŸš€ What This Survey Offers

<details>
<summary><b>ğŸ“š Comprehensive Taxonomy</b></summary>

- Unified framework organizing 300+ papers across planning, tool-use, search, memory, and multi-agent systems
- Clear distinction between in-context and post-training optimization approaches
- Systematic coverage from foundational capabilities to advanced multi-agent collaboration

</details>

<details>
<summary><b>ğŸ”¬ Domain-Specific Insights</b></summary>

- Deep dive into how agentic reasoning is instantiated across diverse domains
- Analysis of evaluation benchmarks spanning core mechanisms and real-world applications
- Case studies demonstrating reasoning mechanisms in action

</details>

<details>
<summary><b>ğŸ”® Future Directions</b></summary>

- Identification of open challenges in personalization, long-horizon interaction, and world modeling
- Discussion of scalable multi-agent training and governance frameworks
- Roadmap for deploying agentic systems in production environments

</details>

### ğŸ’¡ Key Insights

> **Agentic reasoning doesn't just extend LLM capabilitiesâ€”it fundamentally transforms them from passive responders to active problem-solvers that continuously learn and adapt through interaction.**

This survey bridges the gap between:
- ğŸ§  **Thoughts** (reasoning & planning) â†”ï¸ ğŸ¬ **Actions** (tool-use & execution)
- ğŸ”¬ **Theory** (methods & frameworks) â†”ï¸ ğŸ­ **Practice** (applications & deployment)
- ğŸ¤– **Individual** agents â†”ï¸ ğŸ‘¥ **Collective** intelligence

